<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,1263,1770]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,326,1423,1449]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Tube smooth, thick-walled, lacks longitudinal ridges, peristomes or alveoli. Opercular peduncle smooth, white. Base of operculum with rounded dorsal process. Operculum one irregular funnel, with apex displaced to ventral side; funnel with 21–47 radii with rounded tips (
<figureCitation box="[1041,1177,1504,1530]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="17.[151,255,1900,1924]" captionTargetBox="[232,1357,184,1872]" captionTargetId="figure-70@17.[228,1358,182,1876]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 4. A–B: Crucigera irregularis, from Alaska, LACM-AHF N2127. A–B, operculum, left and right view. C–D: Crucigera websteri, from California, LACM-AHF N8819. C–D, operculum, lateral and apical view. E: Crucigera zygophora, from Alaska, LACM-AHF N2128. E, operculum, lateral view. F: Crucigera zygophora, from California, LACM- AHF N412. F, operculum, lateral view." pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Figs 4A–B</figureCitation>
). Collar with bayonet chaetae, with 2–3 blunt-short teeth and minute accessory teeth, distal blade smooth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,1263,1770]" box="[198,1410,1583,1610]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,301,1583,1609]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Habitat.</emphasis>
Depth: 
<quantity box="[396,502,1584,1610]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.85" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="5.7" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" unit="m" value="58.5" valueMax="60.0" valueMin="57.0">57–60 m</quantity>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Imajima, M. &amp; ten Hove, H. A." box="[515,929,1584,1610]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="35 - 66" refId="ref35039" refString="Imajima, M. &amp; ten Hove, H. A. (1984) Serpulinae (Annelida, Polychaeta) from the Truk Islands, Ponape and Majuro Atoll, with some other new Indo-Pacific records. Proceedings of the Japanese Society Systematic Zoology, 27, 35 - 66." type="journal article" year="1984">ten Hove and Jansen-Jacobs (1984)</bibRefCitation>
recorded it down to 
<specimenCount box="[1172,1254,1584,1610]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="generic">
<quantity box="[1172,1250,1584,1610]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7399999999999998" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" unit="m" value="274.0">274 m</quantity>
